.TH UNIPROT 4 2000-1月 "protein.seqs" "protein.seqs"
.SH NAME
protein.seqs \- populate all protein fasta sequence from the given uniprot database reader
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fIprotein.seqs(\fBuniprot\fR as any, 
\fBextractAll\fR as boolean = FALSE, 
\fBtitle\fR as string = "<uniprot_id> <fullname>", 
[\fB<Environment>\fR]);\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
populate all protein fasta sequence from the given uniprot database reader
.PP
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
\fBuniprot\fB \fR\- a collection of the uniprot protein @\fBT:SMRUCC.genomics.Assembly.Uniprot.XML.entry\fR data.. 
.PP
.PP
\fBextractAll\fB \fR\- populate the sequence with all uniprot accession id. 
.PP
.PP
\fBtitle\fB \fR\- 
 the fasta title header template, data keys for template could be:
 
 1. uniprot_id
 2. fullname
 3. name
 4. ncbi_taxid
 5. organism
 6. ec_number
 7. go_id
 8. gene_name
 9. ORF
 10. subcellular_location
 11. db_xrefs...
. 
.PP
.PP
\fBenv\fB \fR\- -. 
.PP
.SH VALUE
.PP
a collection of the @\fBT:SMRUCC.genomics.SequenceModel.FASTA.FastaSeq\fR that export from the given protein set.
 
 the generated fasta sequence header title in format: \fBuniprot_id|db_xref|protein function\fR.
 the db_xref is optional if the parameter "db_xref" is not be omited.
.PP
.SH SEE ALSO
uniprot
.SH FILES
.PP
seqtoolkit.dll
.PP
